00:44:12.890 --> 00:44:14.825
of the kids in San Bernardino.

00:44:14.825 --> 00:44:16.015
JAMES FALLOWS: Yeah.

00:44:16.015 --> 00:44:17.473
DEBORAH FALLOW:
Which is an example

00:44:17.473 --> 00:44:23.150
of a rising up of civic groups
with a direction and a purpose.

00:44:23.150 --> 00:44:25.250
San Bernardino is a
really troubled town.

00:44:25.250 --> 00:44:27.920
And the kids who grew up there--

00:44:27.920 --> 00:44:32.540
let's call them 30-year-olds,
plus or minus five years--

00:44:32.540 --> 00:44:34.250
whom we met and
spent a lot of time

00:44:34.250 --> 00:44:38.810
with, are so tired of
people nay-saying their town

00:44:38.810 --> 00:44:42.950
and feel that they have an
opportunity and an obligation

00:44:42.950 --> 00:44:44.910
to make things
better in that town.

00:44:44.910 --> 00:44:46.110
So they got together.

00:44:46.110 --> 00:44:47.930
They were primarily artists.

00:44:47.930 --> 00:44:49.520
And they formed a
little group, which

00:44:49.520 --> 00:44:50.970
Americans are great at doing.

00:44:50.970 --> 00:44:53.600
They're forming new
groups, not bowling groups,

00:44:53.600 --> 00:44:55.160
but other kinds of groups.

00:44:55.160 --> 00:44:59.540
And the purpose of what these
kids did was the end of it

00:44:59.540 --> 00:45:05.090
was to bring into the
mind-share of high school kids

00:45:05.090 --> 00:45:06.710
the importance of voting.

00:45:06.710 --> 00:45:09.590
And the way they got there
was a kind of pied piper

00:45:09.590 --> 00:45:12.290
movement starting with
cleaning up the parks.

00:45:12.290 --> 00:45:14.870
And they eventually,
as artists, they'd

00:45:14.870 --> 00:45:18.980
draw murals instead of
graffiti and bad graffiti.

00:45:18.980 --> 00:45:20.600
They'd draw nice graffiti.

00:45:20.600 --> 00:45:24.161
And they eventually had groups
of young kids following them

00:45:24.161 --> 00:45:24.660
around.

00:45:24.660 --> 00:45:29.330
And then they would have
fairs and festivals that

00:45:29.330 --> 00:45:30.800
were based around
music, and kind

00:45:30.800 --> 00:45:34.520
of earning the goodwill of
the young people in the town,

00:45:34.520 --> 00:45:37.381
and then made a video
very age appropriate

00:45:37.381 --> 00:45:39.130
that they could take
into the high schools

00:45:39.130 --> 00:45:42.965
to start to imprint on them
the importance of-- you

00:45:42.965 --> 00:45:45.260
want to get to the end of
this, you've got to vote.

00:45:45.260 --> 00:45:47.720
And you've got to understand
your civic responsibility

00:45:47.720 --> 00:45:48.380
there.

00:45:48.380 --> 00:45:51.040
So it's like what do
you call that group?

00:45:51.040 --> 00:45:52.880
I mean they say we are
not an organization.

00:45:52.880 --> 00:45:54.360
We are a movement.

00:45:54.360 --> 00:45:59.120
And we saw many examples of
similar kinds of things, where

00:45:59.120 --> 00:46:01.160
people would get
together for some purpose

00:46:01.160 --> 00:46:02.540
and banding together.

00:46:02.540 --> 00:46:05.060
So it's not a bowling league.

00:46:05.060 --> 00:46:10.997
But it is a group with a
purpose of doing something.

00:46:10.997 --> 00:46:13.580
JAMES FALLOWS: We could give you
a million more illustrations,

00:46:13.580 --> 00:46:14.750
but I won't.

00:46:14.750 --> 00:46:16.524
Yeah.

